    {
      "lineNumber": 28,
      "text": "          At 11:55 P.M., July 11, I took a phone call from",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 29,
      "text": "[REDACTED] of the Laurel, Maryland, Police Department. Sergeant",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 30,
      "text": "[REDACTED] said that he had examined the \"flying disc.\" He said that it",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 31,
      "text": "had been made from a Gulf Oil sign and the top of a garbage can and",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 32,
      "text": "had been painted with aluminum paint. It had been recently painted b7c",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 33,
      "text": "because the paint was still wet. Attached to it were a dry cell",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 34,
      "text": "battery, a flashlight bulb, some wires and a buzzer. He asked if",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 35,
      "text": "the Bureau was sending anyone out to look at it. I told him that",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
